#Install and Configure 

sudo apt install software-properties-common  
  
wget -q -O - https://packages.grafana.com/gpg.key | sudo apt-key add -  
sudo add-apt-repository "deb https://packages.grafana.com/oss/deb stable main"  
sudo apt update  
apt-cache policy grafana  
sudo apt install grafana  

#install grafana pie chart plugin  
sudo grafana-cli plugins install grafana-piechart-panel  

#start grafana server  
sudo systemctl start grafana-server  
#enble grafana server at startup  
sudo systemctl enable grafana-server  
#check status of grafana server  
sudo systemctl status grafana-server  
  
  
As an end result you should be able to reach your grafana endpoint by calling it in a browser window: IP:3000  
By default port 3000 is used then default user is admin and the password is admin, which is strongly recommend to change to much stronger password.  
Also make sure that your firewall allows you to connect to your grafana endpoint.
